ies and priorities of Transport for Buckinghamshire and Rail and Bus companies operating in Aylesbury Vale. </span></p><p style="font-size:14pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">1.3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Act as expert passengers to local public transport service provid</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">ers on all </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">relevant aspects of transport provision and transport </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">infrastructure</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">1.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Will, where possible, pursue individual complaints, and these may be used to illustrate concerns about general operation.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">1.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Champion the interest of passengers in gaining equal</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> access to transport and transport services through Aylesbury Vale</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">1.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Champion such interests by:</span></p><p style="font-size:14pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.44pt; padding-left:6.56pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Consulting with, and advising BCC/TfB and transport providers</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.44pt; padding-left:6.56pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Having input into the transport plans of the above organisations</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.44pt; padding-left:6.56pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Identifying key issues and drawin</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">g up work plans</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.44pt; padding-left:6.56pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Reporting back on service performance, reliability and customer perception</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">1.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Actively engage with Parish Councils and Local Area Forums throughout the Vale</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">1.8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Liaising with Passenger Focus groups on strategic issues as appropriate</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">1.9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Actively engag</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">e with national transport organisations where appropriate</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">AVTUG has a committee of 10 and meeting attendance varying from 25 to 45.</span><a name="_GoBack"></a></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">AVTUG’s response to the committee’s points:</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">How do Government and Local Authorities identify demand for passenger </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">transport in isolated communities (including rural and urban areas and island communities)?</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">There is a need for longer term planning than pre</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">sently exists. Buckinghamshire C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">ounty </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">ouncil has no long term plan for transport.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">AVTUG identify 4 categories of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">demand for travel:</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Medical </span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Shopping</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Friends</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Relatives</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">AVTUG recognises the social and economic benefits that access to tranport brings to both individuals and communities.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">To what extent are the needs of different groups of passengers (e.g. people with di</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">sabilities, older people, young people) taken into account in determining the provision of public transport to isolated communities?</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Insufficiently</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> – for example</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">:</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Dial a ride at its worst can charge up to £30 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">for a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">return </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">fare to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> travel between an outlying</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> village and the county town. The situation is particu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">larly difficult in the northern</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">, less populated, part of Aylesbury Vale.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Marsh village lost its bus service and 5 car</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">less households </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">were left without any means of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">travelling out from their small </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">community.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">A new secondary school, on a new estate on the edge of Aylesbury town, is due to open in September 2013. As of early August no transport arrangements had been announced for its new students.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">There is a perception that profits come before service</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> to the public.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">What are the main challenges associated with providing better and more consistent bus and rail services to isolated communities? How can these challenges be overcome?</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">The cost of providing them.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">The lack of volunteers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> .This is not due to apath</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">y, more volunteer fatigue. Buckinghamshire</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">already </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">boasts twice the national average of volunteers in the community.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">How effectively do Community Transport services address the needs of passengers in isolated communities? How cou</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">ld Community Transport be improved?</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Larger communities, such as Wendover and Winslow already have community buses. This does not appear to be the solution for smaller more isolated communities given costs and volunteer </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">issues referred to above.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Local Area </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Fora already offer small cash incentives to local transport initiatives but these are necessarily limited.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">To what extent should passengers in isolated communities be expected to rely on taxis and other demand-responsive transport services?</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Please see refe</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">rence to Dial a Ride services above. They are demand led, but their costs can be prohibitive. In such situations they are no answer to social isolation.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">What are the main challenges associated with funding transport services in isolated communities? How ca</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">n these services be made more affordable?</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">A long-term plan for transport by the county council would be a useful start. At present planning for the future is apparently too often influenced by more immediate financial considerations.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-style:italic">August 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:14pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>